<br>
Your ideas are great... and help a lot.  When I started this discussion, everything was up in the air, but I had to put something on paper to get the ball rolling.  So I did.  And, I got feedback which caused me to change some of the things.  And again... and again... and again.  This is going to be a long process of revisions before it becomes something that will please most of the people.  The mission will never please all of the people, but that is ok.<br>
<br>
I totally agree with you on the 46 to 59 part.  I keep struggling with getting rid of the 30 to 45 group of people because I do not want to look like a jerk that comes along and takes people from their happy guilds at level 46.  That is why I wanted to include people from level 30 up.  But, the more I think about it, the more I believe that the guild school should concentrate only on levels 46 to 59.  I will give this a great deal more thought before I decide though.<br>
<br>
Also, you showed a lot of anger towards the idea of creating uber guild ready players.  I can understand this because I have some what familar beliefs.  That being said, I wanted to point out that guild school is not about creating mindless players.  There will be those that graduate from guild school and do not go on to &quot;uber&quot; guilds.  Not because they are not good enough, but because they do not choose to play in an &quot;uber&quot; way.  There is nothing wrong with playing in a family style guild, and I would like to think that when people graduate from guild school, they would have the opportunity to choose whether their information be submitted to an &quot;uber&quot; guild or a &quot;family&quot; guild.  Game play style is always the players choice.  The guild school is just there to help the players develop their skills to function in a guild more effectively.  There would never be any time that an officer would tell a member of guild school how to live their life or anything like that.  The officers would simply instruct the members of guild school on how to setup for certain types of raids, how to react in a situation gone wrong, and so on.<br>
